      "text": [
        " : سَأَلْتُ أَبَا عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ عَنِ اَلْحُجَّاجِ مِنَ اَلْكُوفَةِ يَبْدَءُونَ بِالْمَدِينَةِ أَفْضَلُ أَوْ بِمَكَّةَ فَقَالَ « بِالْمَدِينَةِ »."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3141 - Safwan narrated from Al-'Iys ibn Al-Qasim, who said:\nI asked Abu Abdullah (as) about the pilgrims from Kufa—whether starting with Medina or Mecca is better.\nImam (as) replied: \"With Medina.\""
        ]
      }
